<userid>108055072073715452271<//userid><date>1457736065063<//date><Resp>None<//Resp><text>I visited Diamond's on Thursday, March 10, 2016 around 7pm. There's no seating ... take out only (but there is plenty of room for at least 4 tables / 16 seats).

The combo burger meal seemed reasonably priced, so I order it  (cheeseburger, med fries, med drink ... $4.99). I saw they also have Parmesan Garlic fries for $1.99 ($0.50 more the reg fries), so I asked for a substitution & I would pay the difference. The cashier wanted to bill me $1.99 extra, no just $0.50. I questioned him about it, he took it to his boss and the boss said to charge me $0.75 extra. OK, I can live with that.

So I pay and he gives me my drink and I wait 10+ minutes for the food, by which time I'm over halfway done with the drink. So when I get the food, I asked for a "top off" (refill), to which I'm told they charge for refills. Wow, their only competition in a 5+ mile radius is a Mexican restaurant and a bar ... and this is the way they do business? Every other burger joint that I've been to in Barstow gives free refills as long as you haven't left the premises.

Oh, and they gave my order to me in a Togo's bag!

The burger was ok, the fries were good and the drink was ... a drink. And I'll never go there again.

JR< /text>< rating>
1</rating>
</record></dataset><record>

<name>Jennifer P< /name><date>1436377286616<//date>< Rating>
1< /Rating>
< Review>
Several years ago, we hired this company as a second estimate on replacing a complete HVAC system.  We were very happy with their price and the quickness of installation.
One year later, the coil unit they installed went out.  I called them, and because the installation was still under warranty, they replaced the part free of charge.
Two years later....the same part went out again.  We called another company (more local to us) to inspect.  They determined that not only was the part faulty, and that this model has a long history of complaints, but that the workmanship done in the attic was so poorly done that it was a hazard, and the entire system would need to be overhauled at nearly the cost of a complete new unit.

I called Dependable to see if there was anything they could do. The woman on the phone was very rude and emphatic that the warranty was expired.  I told her this is the second time this part has completely failed in 5 years. We had confirmation there is something wrong with the part they installed, AND the workmanship, and shouldn't they at least give us a credit toward repair, or actually replace the part, knowing now that they replaced the broken unit with another faulty part?  She said no, they would not.  I indicated to her that they had just earned a bad review if they could not stand by their products and service.

I have now had a second opinion by another company, which not only concluded that the part itself is still under warranty and could be replaced for the cost of labor and new freon (still several thousand dollars), but that the workmanship done by Dependable was indeed shoddy and would need to be redone, now costing us more money to remedy.</Review>

< Text>
I was very skeptical about using this flower shop, just because I have called and placed orders at about 4 different flowers shops this year and have not been one bit happy with any of the floral arrangements that were delivered. All I can say is that my search for a flower shop is finally over!! I had flowers delivered to my mother today and she called me as soon as she received them and told me that, from all of the flowers that I have ever sent her, these were the most beautiful ones she has ever received!! She said that all of the flowers were beautiful, colorful, fresh looking and smelt incredible, unlike the other flowers that she has received in the past from other flower shops where they had brown edges or missing petals. She also loved the purple vase the flowers came in, said it was a different touch/look from the regular clear ginger vase that flowers usually come in. I asked my mom to send me a picture of the arrangement and I was wowed when I received the picture. I literally went back into Edelweiss' website to pull up the picture of the arrangement that I had ordered (Teleflora's Fresh Flourish Bouquet) and pulled up my mom's picture of the flowers that she received today and put both pictures side by side. All I can say is that my mom received exactly what I payed and hoped for!! Every single flower was arranged EXACTLY as it did on the picture of their website. It was an exact replica!! All the other flower shops that I used in the past never sent me the exact arrangement as what was shown on their website. They always used different flowers from what showed on the picture, different vases, and received smaller size arrangements than what was shown on their website. Edelweiss' website has the actual measurements of each arrangement and my moms' flowers were the exact size as what was mentioned on their website!! And one more thing to add, they delivered the flowers to my mom right on time!! I am a very happy customer and will definitely shop here again!!
If you are wanting to send a special person some beautiful flowers, without getting ripped off, or deal with any stress or headaches, this is the place to shop at!! I strongly recommend this flower shop!!!<//Text>

< Review>
We ordered balloons for my nephew's first birthday and Liz did an excellent job. She chose a nice variety of kids' balloons, brought a nice complementary flower arrangement, delivered on time and even helped tie the balloons around our party area when she dropped off to us at the park! We will definitely be using Edelweiss for our future flower or balloon needs.

I notice some reviews complaining about the answering service after hours. I think this issue has been addressed, because when I ordered Liz gave me a different number in case I needed to call before they opened in the morning (we had a morning party). I did happen to call to change the drop off to the park when I realized I had no way to drive 20 helium balloons to the park. Timothy Riley</username>
<Date>1516766797693</Date>< rate>
3< /rate>
< Text>
We stopped by this place on the way to Redding from Sacramento.  I had never heard of it but gave it a shot even though it was located in a gas station.  It is set up like  a Subway but the sandwiches seemed a little better.   The meat was fresher as was the veggies though I can't say that the place looked as clean as I would have liked.

My daughter in-law got a Chinese Chicken salad and said that it was tasty.  My son had a turkey club and thought that it was just mediocre.  I was not very hungry and was pleased to find out that they offered "mini" sized sandwiches  which is half of a "regular" one (they also sell a large).  My chicken salad Sammy was good with big chunks of meat and not a lot of mayo.

Like Subway you can make it as healthy or as filled with stuff as you want.  All in all it was good but I can't say that it was anything special.</Text>

< review>
I needed a helmet and started browsing around, they had top-tier helmets but nothing less than $60. I just needed something basic, didn't have extra cash to spend on a premium helmet. On our way our the owner flagged us down and said he has some on sale for half off in the back. He walks back and pulls out what looks like a big screen TV box full of helmets.

He pulls a helmet. Perfect size, perfect color, perfect style. Its got a tiny scuff on the top less than 1/4 inch long, but that's it. He said these were some of the imperfect ones left from a wholesale event.

This guy is one of the best salesmen I have ever experienced. He made sure all of our needs were met including affordability, and could spot our concerns from a mile a way without us saying a word.

I'm not sure about the rest of the staff, but I had nothing but an excellent experience. Will be back.</review>

<text>If I could give SoCal Smiles Dentistry 6 stars I would! This review is long overdue as I have been a patient here for several years. <time>1464634794061</time><Name>CHA Racing< /Name><text>I'm going to say 4 stars because the items were cheap, they are durable, they do look excellent, and they were fairly simple to install. I'm going to take away 1 star from the 5 due to the fact that, it was damaged in one little spot, and they don't come with any "REAL" instructions. I can't be mad about the fact that they were not exact sizes and that I needed to do modifications to the kit that would make it go on my car. It states in the description, "have a body shop install it for you" it also states, "trimming may be required". So for the people that are giving ED 1 star and complaining about the fitment, you'll need to read more into it next time. Luckily I did some body work schooling a few years back so the trimming and modifications to fit was not at all a big deal for me due to my past experience. Do I recommend this product? Yes & No. I'd say "YES" if you are able to except the fact that it needs modifications and you are able to do it yourself, or if you are having a professional install it, "NO" if you don't have too much knowledge in body work without the funds to have it professionally installed. Purchased on eBay, Picked up In person. I got a new stylish bumper cover from Extreme Dimensions. Wow. They are huge! I had no idea how large the company was, I knew it wasn't some guy in his garage but I just expect this. Very Professional. I drove 3 hours each way to save $ on freight. GPS guided me to a warehouse shipping industrial area. NOTE it is marked "ED" on the Corner of the building but if you're lucky enough to go there in person you'll note The cool rides out front. Clearly the employees use their product.  I should have written the name of the person from recieption, She was very helpful and welcoming. She explained it would take about 30 min. to have my part brought out, so expect this. The company is huge and they ship lots if products world wide. Similar manufacturers would never let an individual pick up a single item. Imagine going to the Ford Factory to pick up your new Mustang. ED is big business with a small shop feel. Kudos.
P r o f e s s i o n a l installation is recommended. It seems the only negative reviews I have seen are from amateur auto body DIY people. I am one too, but I also have reasonable expectations. YouTube Videos make it look easy so I wanta give it a shot. I know if I do it my self it won't look as perfect as the examples of their product I have seen in magazines or at car shows. I'll post photos later. Show you how I did.
HIGHLY Recommend.< /text>

<Date>1582155524783</Date>< Review>
In the Bay Area, boba places vary from the powdery teas at Quickly, all the way to the finely crafted teas and purees at Asha, Teaspoon and Boba Guys. This spot would probably rate right in the middle of those places except that the unfriendly customer service puts it at the low side of the middle.

The Boba tea itself was decent. I got an iced Taro with black boba. They made it with some syrup and not powder so it tasted better than others that I've had. I didn't specify a sweetness but the sweetness was just right for my moderate sweet preferences.

However I would be likely to try a new place before going back because of the unfriendly service. The owner ran my credit card as a debit. When he asked for my pin I told him I wanted to run it as a credit. He acted like that wasn't possible but then I hit the green button that skipped the pin request and it ran as a credit.

He could have politely told me that he doesn't accept credit and asked me to cancel and run it as a debit.  but instead he grumbled about the processing fee and kind of thrust the receipt at me to sign. I'm not even a person that holds a grudge and probably would have got over it pretty quickly. But that was the only interaction we had. He didn't even greet me when I walked in the door and made me wait while he continued to do whatever he was doing on his phone. I am honestly not even someone who is super harsh on workers because I know that being in the food business is not easy. But with only so-so products and that kind of interaction being my only interaction, I will probably just go ahead and try a different place next time.< /Review>

110336700528800100628</user>
<Text>Went here because we we're craving some Bao Buns and some Taiwanese popcorn style chicken on the way home. We were reading some reviews and it caught our attention that it was owned and ran by a gourmet chef. So we we're pretty excited. It was a bit on the pricey side, but we thought "hey if it's good, it'll be worth it". My honest opinion...it was ok. The meat was tender and the Bao was fine, but it lacked flavor and it wasn't that big. The chicken was crispy, but a bit greasy and a little too salty. Drinks were standard tea with syrup, and they were smaller than your average milk tea places (8 oz for medium and 16oz for large).  Maybe other people will have other opinions and I'm just a tough critic, but all in all...I thought it was ok, but not worth the price. My expectations were too high at $30 for 2 baos, 2 drinks and chicken. Don't be fooled if you think you'll save some money with the combo, the price is the same if you were to buy it seperately. Also another thing was that all the utensils and napkins we're kept behind the counter away from reach. When I got to the car, I wasn't given any utensils nor napkins. Would it kill you to add some forks and napkins without us having to ask?

Edit: I apologize to the owner, I got the drink size mixed up. He is correct, it is not an 8 oz cup, but rather a 16 oz. However, I stand by my word about my honest review of the food. I felt like I overpaid for something that is what I can best describe a "snack" and the quality was "ok". I've eaten at plenty of  Bao Buns and Taiwanese fried chicken and this is definitely on the lower scale compared to them. But hey, everyone is entitled to their own opinion. This is a very old hotel in much need of a refresh. The rooms are very dark. The carpet needs to be replaced. The wallpaper is peeling.  The bathroom was so small you nearly had to climb into the tub to shut the door.On the plus side, the lobby and the breakfast room were bright and cheery. 4< /Rate>
<Text>I spent four nights here. It was a double room, and I was attending a company-sponsored event.

You will get the basics. There is a hot tub and a shower. You get bar soap, shampoo, conditioner, mouthwash, and body lotion. You only get one set though, for a double-occupancy room.

You get a coffee machine, and two sets of condiments. You also get both regular and decaffeinated.

The rooms come with breakfast. You get tea and coffee, yogurt, bagels, donuts, and waffles. Breakfast is 6 to 10.

Outside of those hours, you need to purchase drinks from a dispenser, which doesn't take all cards and rejected my bills. There is a convenience store nearby, and food is a mile away.

Checkout is at 11, so factor that into your schedule.< /Text>< pictures>
None</pictures>

< text>
The bad: Room had very strong musty old smell for non smoking that I couldn't get rid of even with air running. Very old motel that has been updated mostly. Internet didn't work. Bedroom and sink area have been updated but the shower is out of the 80s. Clearly on their to do list, but not renovated yet.Front lobby looked like a mixture of renovated and disrepair. Exterior door doesn't seal, large visible gap at bottom.

The good: Bed and pillows are very comfy. AC works well.  Rooms come with fridge, hair dryer, safe, coffee machine, TV, phone,desk. As a cheap place to sleep, this gets the job done. So close to being a good hotel with little fixes. Nice hot tub.<//text>

<Rating>4<//Rating>< Text>
Functional. I would describe this as a no frills location. It's generally more reasonably priced than most chain hotels in silicon valley but you get what you pay for. Rooms are clean and comfortable but many of them could do with refurbishing. There's a small gym and an open - air pool and a laundry (that was out of order last time I was there). There is a reasonable selection for breakfast but they don't have an on-site restaurant. Mercado Plaza is 5-10 minutes walk and has some eating options.</Text>

This hotel was pretty average. Good location, but the room was a bit musty. I had mis-booked my visit by a day so I did very much appreciate that they didn't bill me for the incorrect day... which they'd have been justified doing.

The single event that made me want to write a review was as follows:

The checkout time listed in the room's information binder was incorrect (written as noon; apparently, in fact,11).

After the concierge lady called to the room to inform me I had over-stayed the checkout time, I confirmed the information I had looked up earlier in their room binder and took a photo.

When I showed it to her she smugly pointed to a printed piece of paper in the corner of the concierge desk that indicated the checkout time in the room books is incorrect... Her tone made it clear that she thought my not knowing they had a such a note elsewhere in the building was ridiculous and unjustifiable on my part.

As an actionable item for management: you could surely just reprint that single binder page for each room.

Anyway, this is just about the only online review I recall ever generating... In that sense this visit was remarkable<//review>

<Rating>4<//Rating>< gmap_id>

< Text>
We booked the hotel as the best deal we could find in the Sunnyvale area. This motel style facility is very well renovated with attractively renovated rooms around a semi-tropical garden with pool. The beds and bedding are excellent, much higher quality than we anticipated. The room also had a good sized modern drinks fridge. The self service breakfast buffet offered great choices including burritos and Jimmy Dean sandwiches on alternate days. Bagels were "real", fresh and with a range of flavors and icings. Unlike most buffets in economy hotels the food was constantly refilled and freshioned. This hotel is a deal!< /Text>

< Text>
As mentioned in other reviews, this hotel has seen better days. The staff is doing what they can, but the venue is beat up and dated. The location is fine for a cheap night for a business trip, but nothing within walking distance (5 blocks) of the hotel. though there is plenty to do and see within driving distance, and easy on & off the 101.

The food is generic and cheap, think from Sam's Club or Costco.

Some of my fellow attendees complained about issues with their rooms, weird stands, odors, etc. Again, for a venue that has not been updated in a decade (perhaps longer) you are going to find these sorts of issues.< /Text>

This was the second time my family and I stayed at the Ramada Silicon Valley/Sunnyvale Inn and we kind of regret staying here. Our stay was for 3 nights but we could easily tell that our room was not cleaned thoroughly for 2 of those 3 days. We even came back to our room one afternoon in a hurry to get ready for my sister's graduation and we found our bathroom door locked. Clean room, good value. Rooms are a little tight and the layout is not the best. Pool is nice, hot tub could be hotter. Gym is very basic, air conditioning not working and the water cooler has been empty for the last 3 days. Regarding the gym, it seems if you are, hmm how shall we say..... rotund and key in a weight above 180 no excersise programs can be entered.

I read other reviews about an ant problem. What I can say is I found one or two very small ants in my room as well as the gym. So nothing too bad, but most likely a problem.

Breakfast was good. Lobby is nice. Beds comfortable.< /Review>

<Text>I feel like I'm staying at a 30 year old Motel 6 in the rural midwest that is the only hotel in 100 miles in either direction. This Ramada is run down, worn out, and tore up. It looks like parts of it were in the process of being renovated and then that idea was abandoned in place.

There are weird noises coming from the walls. My neighbor is having a quiet conversation with his wife and I can hear every word. The mini-fridge thing is plugged in but not working.

<GmapID>0x808fc9d8a35c9ac5:0x63566488f4f83195<//GmapID><pics>None</pics><Name>Joshua Coward<//Name><resp>None</resp>< rating>
2<//rating>
< Review>
This was close to the least expensive place I could find in the Bay Area. The accommodations were a little less than what I was expecting. For the price I knew I wasn't going to get a 5 star room but was definitely underwhelmed when I arrived. I shared my room with someone so there were two full beds. The room itself was very small. They could barely fit a desk and chair in it with the two beds. The tv was a scant 30 inches. The beds were not very comfortable unless you like a very firm mattress. But the real killer were the pillows. You know the ones you have kept in the closet for 20 years and are all lumpy? Times that by about 3 and you'll reach the level of crap that these pillows were. The bathroom is very very small. I'm not a small guy butt in not huge either. I was definitely worried that I would hit my head on the light fixture in the shower room. Couple that with no exhaust fan and about enough room to turn around and you get one of the worst bathrooms I've ever seen in a hotel. But apart from all the negatives, I only wanted it as a place to sleep and shower. And that's why I gave it 2 stars instead of 1. It succeeded in letting me sleep and shower and get the heck outta there. Also, the free breakfast is pretty subpar, expect to be going out for every meal.<//Review>

<name>Y Liu (SMF)< /name><review>In Dec 2014, I had stayed at Ramada Inn Sunnyvale for 3 weeks during my business trip there. After reading some "horrible" reviews here, I started to wonder if I made a wrong choice.

The sign said something like newly renovated, so the room didn't look like old.  I got a quiet and a clean room. During the first night I checked in, my digital safe in the room was not able to use, the staff fixed it for me immediately. Later during the last week of my stay, the remote control was dead and I got a replacement immediately too. The service was good enough.

Wi-fi is very good.

Though the refrigerator was broken and the air conditioner leaked, wetting the carpet around the window, it's not what I really cared about. I didn't ask for help.

You can easily get on Lawrence Expressway and Freeway 101 with several minutes. Location is convenient.

There is a AMC theater square and several restaurant and a Walmart around. They are with in a walking distance but I still drove there because of rain.  There is a 7-11 just outside the inn.

The breakfast has sausage, cereals, waffle, bagel, coffee, fruits, cocoa, yogurt, and juice. It's not bad, though after 1 week with the same breakfast, I usually go out and eat at somewhere else.

All in all, to me it's just a better motel than others.<//review><Resp>None</Resp><Rate>4</Rate><userid>101253192528621408994</userid></record></dataset><record>

< userid>
112416262467735498857<//userid>
<Name>Ryan Crompton< /Name><Time>1425958377470<//Time>< rate>
3< /rate>
< text>
When writing a review, it's good to come to the table with the appropriate expectations. I wouldn't ding the rental car company for not renting me a Mercedes at Hyundai prices. Likewise, it's unreasonable to expect to get Marriott-level service at $100 a night.

I've stayed at this hotel three times; in each case, the Avatar or Marriott near here were either sold out or had rooms at 3x the cost of the Ramada.

I have a short list of complaints. Here they are:
-- No weather stripping on the doors. This allows you to clearly hear everything going on in the parking lot. It also results in condensation inside your room in the morning if you don't run the heater at night.
-- The shower head is at about 5 feet.
-- The bathroom door on my latest stay actually rubs against the toilet when closing. Needless to say, it's cramped.
-- Internet is totally and needlessly bad. Given that they're a stone's throw away from the people that built the gear they're using, it's inexcusable. And should management read this, your Internet has two problems -- AP's are located in rooms, such that anybody can unplug the cable, and anyone else who has the misfortune of associating to that AP can't get connected. Second problem -- you're running 40 MHz bands on your 2.4GHz frequencies, which is triggering a massive noisy neighbor problem. On my most recent stay, I could see 4 AP's, all of which were overlapping on the center channels (5-7), and it was essentially broken the whole time I was there.

Breakfast is 'meh' at best.

There are a few things within walking distance. There's a shopping center on the way to Mission College with quite a few places to eat (SmokeEaters). It's about a 10-minute walk. I didn't feel unsafe walking in this neighborhood.

If you've got a reason to be at the EMC / McAfee / Intel / Mission College site, this is a decent place to stay if the Internet's working, especially if you want to save your company a few bucks.< /text>
